[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mWhen I first started learning[m
[32m+[m[32m            how to code,[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mthere were countless times when I picked it up then gave[m
[32m+[m[32mup, again and again. This is a common story amongst[m
[32m+[m[32mself-taught coders. Looking back, after teaching so many[m
[32m+[m[32mstudents, I finally realise what‚Äôs going on. A lot of[m
[32m+[m[32mbeginners start learning to code by picking an arbitrary[m
[32m+[m[32mlanguage and following along with a bunch of tutorials.[m
[32m+[m[32mCopying code, line by line, sometimes writing code to work[m
[32m+[m[32mout prime numbers, other times to find all the even[m
[32m+[m[32mnumbers.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mBut you know what? I can find prime numbers a lot faster[m
[32m+[m[32mby Googling for it and picking out even numbers is not all[m
[32m+[m[32mthat interesting.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mHere‚Äôs the truth. If you are learning to code for the sake of[m
[32m+[m[32mlearning to code, it‚Äôll be pretty difficult for you to get good[m
[32m+[m[32mat it. Skills that require a lot of time to hone, like[m
[32m+[m[32mprogramming, will eat into your pool of internal[m
[32m+[m[32mmotivation. Something from within that makes you forget[m
[32m+[m[32mto eat and sleep. I can honestly say that coding on my own[m
[32m+[m[32mprojects is one of the most enjoyable things I do.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mCopyright ¬© The App Brewery                                      8[m
[32m+[m[32m                                                                               www.appbrewery.com[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m   It combines logical thinking with creativity, and at the end,[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mLearning to code is a bit like you will have made something. In most cases, something[m
[32m+[m[32m   that the world has never seen. Something that could make[m
[32m+[m[32m going to the gym. your life easier or more enjoyable. Something that could[m
[32m+[m[32m   make loads of people's lives easier and more enjoyable. It‚Äôs[m
[32m+[m[32m   like making a crazy-beautiful custom motorbike in your[m
[32m+[m[32m   garage, without needing the garage or spending a cent on[m
[32m+[m[32m   the components.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m   This is what motivates most people. The creating part. The[m
[32m+[m[32m   making part. So I urge you to start learning to code by[m
[32m+[m[32m   following a tutorial that makes something, anything.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m   Of course, it‚Äôs unlikely that at the beginning, you'll be able[m
[32m+[m[32m   to code up Clash of Clans or League of Legends. But you‚Äôll[m
[32m+[m[32m   be able to make something interesting. It could be a dice[m
[32m+[m[32m   game or a flash-card app. But as long at the end of the[m
[32m+[m[32m   tutorial, you‚Äôll have made something you can use and play[m
[32m+[m[32m   with, then you‚Äôll be far more motivated to code to the end.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m   During all our courses, we always tell our students to think[m
[32m+[m[32m   up a simple app that they want to make. Something that[m
[32m+[m[32m   uses the skills that they‚Äôve learned during the course but[m
[32m+[m[32m   will also stretch them a little because they have to find out[m
[32m+[m[32m   how to include some new functionality.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m   We had a student who went on to make an app that wakes[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mCopyright ¬© The App Brewery                                                                        9[m
[32m+[m[32m                                                                               www.appbrewery.com[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m   them up a minute earlier every day to ease the transition to[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mLearning to code is a bit like an earlier waking time. There‚Äôs a student who made a[m
[32m+[m[32m   custom slideshow app as a mother‚Äôs day present. Someone[m
[32m+[m[32m going to the gym. else made an app that is a timer for making perfect steaks[m
[32m+[m[32m   based on their weight and thickness.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m   There are no limits on your imagination. It will be difficult[m
[32m+[m[32m   when you start working on your own app because there are[m
[32m+[m[32m   no step-by-step instructions, but it will also bring about the[m
[32m+[m[32m   biggest improvement in your coding ability.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m‚Äú You don‚Äôt hire for skills, you    ‚Äú[m
[32m+[m[32m        hire for attitude. You can[m
[32m+[m[32m        always teach skills.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m            Simon Sinek[m
