[32m+[m[32m                     RULE THREE[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThere is No ‚ÄúPerfect‚Äù[m
[32m+[m[32m Language to Learn[m
[32m+[m[32m                                                                           www.appbrewery.com[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mWhenever I do large talks,[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mthere will always be one person who asks me ‚Äúwhich[m
[32m+[m[32mprogramming language should I start learning first‚Äù?[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThere is this common perception that somewhere out there[m
[32m+[m[32mlies a perfect language for beginner programmers. Some[m
[32m+[m[32margue it‚Äôs Python, some say it‚Äôs Javascript.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mBut I say they‚Äôre all wrong.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mA programming language is simply a tool. It is no different[m
[32m+[m[32mfrom any other tool in your hardware box. If you want to[m
[32m+[m[32mhammer a nail, you should be using a hammer. If you want[m
[32m+[m[32mto fix your water pipes, you‚Äôll probably need a spanner.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mYes, it‚Äôs possible to hammer in a nail using the side of the[m
[32m+[m[32mspanner and the same programming language can be used[m
[32m+[m[32mto solve different types of problems. The carpenter will tell[m
[32m+[m[32myou that his favourite tool is a hammer and the plumber[m
[32m+[m[32mwill say it‚Äôs the spanner, but it still doesn‚Äôt make it the ‚Äúbest[m
[32m+[m[32mtool to fix things‚Äù.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mCopyright ¬© The App Brewery                                                                    12[m
[32m+[m[32m                                                                               www.appbrewery.com[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m   A web developer will tell you that JavaScript is the best[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mLearning to code is a bit like language to learn for a beginner. A statistician will advise[m
[32m+[m[32m   you that you‚Äôll be best served with the R programming[m
[32m+[m[32m going to the gym. language. But at the end of the day, all that matters is what[m
[32m+[m[32m   you are trying to do with your tool. If you want to make iOS[m
[32m+[m[32m   apps, then learn Swift. If you want to make websites, you‚Äôll[m
[32m+[m[32m   need JavaScript.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m   But the good news is the core programming concepts:[m
[32m+[m[32m   loops, conditionals, functions, etc. they‚Äôre all the same. The[m
[32m+[m[32m   difference is mostly syntactical.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m   In English, we have werewolves, in German they have[m
[32m+[m[32m   Werw√∂lfe. It‚Äôs still the same shirt-ripping mammal that[m
[32m+[m[32m   comes out during a full moon, it‚Äôs just spelt differently.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m   Printing to the console in Swift:[m
[32m+[m[32m   print(‚ÄúHello Werewolves‚Äù)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m   Printing to the console in Java:[m
[32m+[m[32m   println(‚ÄúHello Werw√∂lfe‚Äù)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m   So, decide on the task that you are trying to accomplish,[m
[32m+[m[32m   then pick the best tool for that task.[m
